<h1>Fuel Injector Calculator</h1>
<p align=3D"justify">Looking to build a car with serious power, and turn he=
ads on the street and strip or racetrack? You need to know the correct size=
d fuel injector that will get you there. What's the most important componen=
t in a racecar? Not the turbo, not the engine, and not the suspension. It's=
 the fuel delivery system.</p>
<p align=3D"justify"><a href=3D"http://www.maperformance.com/collections/fu=
el-injectors/" target=3D"_blank" rel=3D"noopener noreferrer">Fuel injectors=
</a> are one of the most important pieces of the puzzle in building a fast =
car. Without correctly sized injectors, the car wont be able to make max po=
wer, and in some cases it wont run at all. It may even do damage if inadequ=
ate fuel enters the engine under heavy load. When shopping for fuel injecto=
rs, you want to consider the flow rates / pressure, impedance, and connecti=
on type</p>
<ul>
<li>
<strong>Flow Rate / PSI</strong> - Referred to in CC (cubic centimeters), t=
his is how much fuel the injector will move over 1 minute.</li>
<li>
<strong>Impedance</strong> - Simply put, it's the electrical resistance of =
the injector. Low impedance injectors are used on high performance applicat=
ions, where high impedance injectors are commonly used on stock application=
s.</li>
<li>
<strong>Connection Type</strong> - Some injectors are universal and must be=
 crimped into the ECU harness to operation, where others are available with=
 plug-and-play connections for simple installations.</li>
</ul>
<p align=3D"justify">We've built this handy <a href=3D"http://www.maperform=
ance.com/collections/fuel-injectors/" target=3D"_blank" rel=3D"noopener nor=
eferrer">Fuel Injector</a> sizing calculator to help you determine how much=
 flow you'll need. Simply enter your goal crank horsepower goal, the number=
 of injectors (cylinders) your engine has, the correct number based on aspi=
ration of your engine, and goal PSI at the rail.&nbsp;Have any questions ab=
out a specific number, or unsure how to use the calculator? Feel free to co=
ntact us today for assistance, and we'll take the stress out of the fuel de=
livery aspect of your build!</p>
<a href=3D"http://www.maperformance.com/collections/fuel-injectors/" target=
=3D"_blank" rel=3D"noopener noreferrer"><img src=3D"https://cdn.shopify.com=
/s/files/1/0890/6136/files/find-your-turbo_c196adff-1893-48d5-a5b7-c69140e9=
7baf.jpg?10315756713066375913" alt=3D"buy fuel injectors" style=3D"border: =
1px solid; width: 350px;"></a>
</div>
<br> <!--Injector Calculator-->
<div id=3D"content" class=3D"col-sm-12">
<h1>Flow Calculator</h1>
<p style=3D"font-size: 12.222222328186035px;"><span style=3D"font-size: 14p=
x;">Looking for 500 horsepower to the rear wheels? How about 1000 horsepowe=
r at the crankshaft? You can determine what size fuel injectors you will ne=
ed by entering a few simple details into our calculator. Explanations of ea=
ch input are below the calculator.</span></p>
<p style=3D"font-size: 12.222222328186035px;"><span style=3D"font-size: 14p=
x;">The inputs are, in order of appearance:</span></p>
<p style=3D"font-size: 12.222222328186035px;"><span style=3D"font-size: 14p=
x;">The number of cylinders in your engine,</span></p>
<p style=3D"font-size: 12.222222328186035px;"><span style=3D"font-size: 14p=
x;">The&nbsp;<strong><em>BASE*</em></strong>&nbsp;fuel pressure you will ru=
n (your fuel pressure at idle), *our calculator assumes a 1:1 rising rate f=
uel pressure regulator for turbo applications</span></p>
<p style=3D"font-size: 12.222222328186035px;"><span style=3D"font-size: 14p=
x;">Engine aspiration, {Turbocharged, Supercharged, and Naturally Aspirated=
 engines have different BSFC=E2=80=99s (see Glossary of Terms for definitio=
ns)}</span></p>
<p style=3D"font-size: 12.222222328186035px;"><span style=3D"font-size: 14p=
x;">Desired horsepower, (The amount of power you desire directly affects th=
e amount of fuel you will need to achieve your goal.)</span></p>
<p style=3D"font-size: 12.222222328186035px;"><span style=3D"font-size: 14p=
x;">Maximum injector duty cycle (IDC) (In order to be conservative, Fuel In=
jector Clinic recommends a maximum duty cycle of 90%.)</span></p>
<p style=3D"font-size: 12.222222328186035px;">&nbsp;</p>
<div class=3D"flow" id=3D"calculator">
<label># of Cylinders <input class=3D"number-only" id=3D"cylinders" name=3D=
"cylinders" type=3D"number" value=3D"4"></label> <label>Fuel Pressure (psi)=
